The paper discusses a decentralized optimization algorithm for solving nonconvex problems, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on solving large-scale machine learning problems. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also relevant as the paper proposes a decentralized variant of an existing algorithm. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses optimization algorithms for neural networks. Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm for controlling decentralized systems.
